description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an exceptional candidate to help shape the future direction of the ophthalmic services at the Oxford Eye Hospital and develop a career pathway enabling clinical, academic and teaching aspirations in a centre of excellence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Oxford Eye Hospital works closely with the University of Oxford, currently&lt;br /&gt;the leading university in the world, thus conferring a wide range of opportunities for collaborations in research and teaching. The post holder would have the opportunity to work in a vibrant and exciting environment within a dynamic consultant team in one of the most attractive cities in the UK, and to be part of shaping a new planned state-of-the-art Oxford Eye Hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and highly motivated Consultant Ophthalmologist to join our established team of 19 Consultants and work in the Eye Emergency Department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Oxford Eye Hospital provides an eye emergency service to the Oxfordshire Population and the wider Thames Valley. We expedite diagnosis and management of otherwise sight-and life threatening conditions by providing rapid access to a Consultant-led Multidisciplinary team. This post is to expand the Consultant Cover, training and supervision of Junior Doctors and Allied Health Professionals and to improve the efficiency of the &lt;br /&gt;department. The post is based at the John Radcliffe Hospital which is a neurosciences centre including neuroradiology as well as a children’s hospital, cancer centre, trauma centre. This post includes a theatre session and peripheral clinic sessions and participating in the consultant on call rota.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must be on the GMC specialist register or be within 6 months of doing so at the time of the interview. Applications from those wishing to work part-time or job share are welcomed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A complimentary sub-specialty interest would be welcomed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that only electronic applications can be accepted for this post.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates are highly recommended to visit the department and hospital and are invited to contact Mrs. Hornby Clinical Lead and Consultant in Emergency Eye Care &amp; Primary Care Ophthalmology via email on stella.hornby@ouh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
